}} }} 'Bromo-DragonFLY' is a psychedelic drug related to the phenethylamine
family. Bromo-DragonFLY is considered an extremely potent hallucinogen, only
slightly less potent than LSD with a normal dose in the region of 200 Î¼g to 800
Î¼g, and it has an extremely long duration of action up to several days. It is explicitly
illegal only in Finland, Sweden, Norway, Denmark and Ireland, although it may be considered a
controlled substance analogue under US and Australian drug laws. Bromo-DragonFLY
has a stereocenter and R-(-)-bromo-DragonFLY is the more active stereoisomer.
